<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1038,2037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,261,1039,1063]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Head</emphasis>
. Brown; eyes of male meeting on meson of head, upper portion of eyes brownish and lowers portion black; ocelli white; antennal scape brown, pedicel brown, flagellum pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1038,2037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,285,1111,1135]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Thorax</emphasis>
. Chestnut, with tergal suture yellowish brown, and sternal suture brown. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1287,1110,1134]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1895,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1874]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 (A – F). Paramaka pearljam, sp. n., imago. A, forewing; B, hind wing; C, detail of penis (ventral view); D, styliger plate (lateral view) (arrow indicating the median projection); E, abdominal color pattern (segments I – VII) (dorsal view); F, styliger plate (ventral view) (arrow indicating median projection)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207730/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1273,1287,1110,1134]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[1322,1338,1110,1134]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
B): forewings hyaline with veins and crossveins yellowish. 
<collectingCountry box="[745,801,1146,1170]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Hind</collectingCountry>
wings: costal projection well developed. Legs: femora, tibia and tarsi yellowish, tarsal claws dissimilar, one hooked apically, other pad–like. Except for apex of femur and base of tibia III tinged with black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1038,2037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,314,1254,1279]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[329,407,1254,1278]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1895,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1874]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 (A – F). Paramaka pearljam, sp. n., imago. A, forewing; B, hind wing; C, detail of penis (ventral view); D, styliger plate (lateral view) (arrow indicating the median projection); E, abdominal color pattern (segments I – VII) (dorsal view); F, styliger plate (ventral view) (arrow indicating median projection)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207730/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Figs. 
<number box="[393,407,1254,1278]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[439,454,1254,1278]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
). All tergites with a dorsal median black band; tergites I and II tinged with brown; III– VI brown with a white anterior band, and IV and V with a white posterior band; VII–X dark brown; in lateral view, II–VI with a white anterior spot, and a small white spot near to spiracles; sternites I–II brown; III–VI brown with two white anterior spots, III and IV with a white posterior band; VII–X dark brown;in some specimens general color of abdomen as in 
<figureCitation box="[423,492,1398,1422]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,976,999]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,965]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[211,1376,193,965]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Imago of Paramaka pearljam, sp. n. (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207731/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[476,492,1398,1422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[626,706,1398,1422]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1895,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1874]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 (A – F). Paramaka pearljam, sp. n., imago. A, forewing; B, hind wing; C, detail of penis (ventral view); D, styliger plate (lateral view) (arrow indicating the median projection); E, abdominal color pattern (segments I – VII) (dorsal view); F, styliger plate (ventral view) (arrow indicating median projection)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207730/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Figs. 
<number box="[691,706,1398,1422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C, 
<number box="[739,754,1398,1422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
D, 
<number box="[790,805,1398,1422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
F): forceps yellowish; styliger plate with a conspicuous and large median projection with apex curved ventrally (indicated by an arrow in 
<figureCitation box="[1071,1137,1434,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1895,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1874]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 (A – F). Paramaka pearljam, sp. n., imago. A, forewing; B, hind wing; C, detail of penis (ventral view); D, styliger plate (lateral view) (arrow indicating the median projection); E, abdominal color pattern (segments I – VII) (dorsal view); F, styliger plate (ventral view) (arrow indicating median projection)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207730/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1123,1137,1434,1458]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D and 
<figureCitation box="[1213,1279,1434,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1895,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1874]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 (A – F). Paramaka pearljam, sp. n., imago. A, forewing; B, hind wing; C, detail of penis (ventral view); D, styliger plate (lateral view) (arrow indicating the median projection); E, abdominal color pattern (segments I – VII) (dorsal view); F, styliger plate (ventral view) (arrow indicating median projection)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207730/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1264,1279,1434,1458]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
F); inner margin of segment I of forceps with short spines; penis rounded on the apex and with a membranous inner projection (
<figureCitation box="[159,227,1506,1530]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1895,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1874]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 (A – F). Paramaka pearljam, sp. n., imago. A, forewing; B, hind wing; C, detail of penis (ventral view); D, styliger plate (lateral view) (arrow indicating the median projection); E, abdominal color pattern (segments I – VII) (dorsal view); F, styliger plate (ventral view) (arrow indicating median projection)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207730/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,227,1506,1530]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Terminal filament broken off.
</paragraph>
